The Katsina state chairman, Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Pastor Nelson Onyekachukwu said reports reaching him from various local council chapters in Katsina showed a peaceful celebration. Speaking with newsmen, Onyekachukwu urged followers of different faiths in the state to continue to live as one for growth and development. He said the prevailing peace in the state has enabled Christians to celebrate Christmas without security hitches. “Information from the local governments across the state indicated that Christmas was celebrated peacefully with no reports of any security issues,” he said. Story of Katsina’s indigenous Christians 65,000 Christians in Katsina state fast, pray for Buhari In North-East, Christmas in a time of insurgency